<sect1 id="GetEspUrl">
  <!-- DNT-Start --><title><emphasis role="bold">GetEspUrl</emphasis></title><!-- DNT-End -->

  <!-- DNT-Start --><para><emphasis>result</emphasis> <emphasis role="bold"> :=
  STD.File.GetEspUrl <indexterm>
      <primary>STD.File.GetEspUrl</primary>
    </indexterm><indexterm>
      <primary>File.GetEspUrl</primary>
    </indexterm> <indexterm>
      <primary>GetEspUrl</primary>
    </indexterm>( [</emphasis> <emphasis>username, userPW </emphasis>
  <emphasis role="bold">]);</emphasis></para><!-- DNT-End -->

  <informaltable colsep="1" frame="all" rowsep="1">
    <tgroup cols="2">
      <colspec colwidth="80.50pt" />

      <colspec />

      <tbody>
        <row>
          <entry><!-- DNT-Start --><emphasis>username</emphasis><!-- DNT-End --></entry>

          <entry>Optional. A <!-- DNT-Start -->STRING<!-- DNT-End --> containing a username to use for
          authenticated access to the <!-- DNT-Start -->ESP<!-- DNT-End --> process. If omitted, it indicates
          that no user authentication is required. </entry>
        </row>

        <row>
          <entry><!-- DNT-Start --><emphasis>userPW</emphasis><!-- DNT-End --></entry>

          <entry>Optional. A <!-- DNT-Start -->STRING<!-- DNT-End --> containing the password to use with the
          user cited in the <emphasis>username</emphasis> argument. If
          <emphasis>username</emphasis> is empty then this is ignored</entry>
        </row>

        <row>
          <entry><!-- DNT-Start -->Return:<emphasis> </emphasis><!-- DNT-End --></entry>

          <entry>GetEspUrl returns a <!-- DNT-Start -->STRING<!-- DNT-End --> containing the full <!-- DNT-Start -->URL<!-- DNT-End --> (including
          <!-- DNT-Start -->HTTP<!-- DNT-End --> scheme and port) to an <!-- DNT-Start -->ESP<!-- DNT-End --> server process. If more than one <!-- DNT-Start -->ESP<!-- DNT-End -->
          process is defined then the first found process is returned. Returns
          an empty string if an <!-- DNT-Start -->ESP<!-- DNT-End --> server process cannot be found in the
          environment.</entry>
        </row>
      </tbody>
    </tgroup>
  </informaltable>

  <para>The <emphasis role="bold">GetEspUrl </emphasis>function returns the
  full <!-- DNT-Start -->URL<!-- DNT-End --> to an <!-- DNT-Start -->ESP<!-- DNT-End --> server process. </para>

  <para>Example:</para>

  <!-- DNT-Start --><programlisting format="linespecific">EspAddress := STD.File.GetEspUrl
</programlisting><!-- DNT-End -->
</sect1>
